                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Right, we benefit from nuke focuses too; but not like wizards do. Wizards can crit innately, and currently have 3 crit AA lines, compared to the 2 crit AA lines other nukers get. Not to mention the little fact their nukes are the best in the game, unfocused. So a wizard can crit for 6.5k, while necros can crit for just over 3k. That's assuming ID4 (not one of the higher % clones), and max nuke crit AAs. So saying crit dots should be gimped to less than half the % wizards get on their crit AAs because we can get nuke crit AAs too isn't a fair and accurate assessment.<br /><br />Still, the fact we do benefit from nuke crit AAs should be considered. After all, wizards aren't going to get anything from Critical Affliction. I can concede that for us to get the same % with Critical Affliction as wizards get for full crit AAs would be unbalanced. Getting 2/3 of the % from CA that wizards get wouldn't, especially considering the current cost in AA points.<br /><br />And no, just scaling back the cost to 2/4/6 to get 2/4/7% wouldn't be enough. Either: leave current cost the same and go with 4/8/13%, or split Critical Affliction into an archetype level skill with 2/4/7% at a cost of 2/4/6 AA and a class level skill that adds an additional 2/2/2 % for 5/5/5 AA. Scale the %s and AA costs how you like, but the end results in % and cost should come out in the neighborhood of 13-15% for 27-30 AA.<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
