                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> The main issue for me is the cost issue.  Too many AA's required for too little gain.  It practically reeks of the current mentality that EQ is supposed to be a endless grind where you spend huge chunks of time for very little fun & benefit.  But then this applies to all the AA's they're releasing this expansion, and not just crit DoTs.<br /><br />For me it has little to do with balance.  I frankly don't care about the numbers anymore, but even if you did, it's the *OVERALL* DPS numbers that you should be worried about and not some issue with not being able to crit as much as wizards on DoTs.  If your overall DPS is on par with wizards then there's no real room to complain.  If not, then maybe DoT crits can be a solution, but insofar as whether that's true I've not yet seen conclusive evidence.<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
