s, we are more a utility class than wizzies are, and we should take this into account, ..... then please give us some better upgrades to utility spells like nightstalker, and some appropriate AAs damnit. right now we are a pure dps class, at least on raids for longterm dmg.<br /><br />8, if all AAs are more expensive now than the old ones been when they introduced AAs, i would agree that crit dots are more expensive, too. i undertstand, that SoE planned that you need 2h to get an AA when they introduced it (lvl 51 to 59 this time). ok, necs never needed such long, but other classes. now, we are all 65 with a hell of AA and we have to pay more because we can do it much faster, thats ok. i understand, that you have to let us grind until next expansion but then for gods sake give us interesting AA we are willing to grind for and not quit the game. you got it SoE?<br /><br />WE JUST LIKE THE SAME CHANCE LIKE NUKERS. AND START BALANCING DPS CLASSES SOE. YOU ARE 2 YEARS BEHIND YOUR ANNOUNCEMENT AND YOU JUST GOT WORSE.<br /><br />Usul<br /><hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />I agree completely, please use this Waldina.<br /><br />I honestly don't care how mamy AA's these cost. The fact is that we (DoT classes) are far below the POTENTIAL to improve ourselves as pure DD classes have had for years. The reason given was that it the programmers weren't able to implement crit DoT's. Now that they can, we should have the same potential to improve our damage as other caster damage classes.<br /><br />Why should we get Crit DoT AA's at the same level as Wizzies or at the very least as much as Mages?<br /><br />DPS point of view:<br />We can't cast 2 spells at the same time. We either choose to cast a DoT with crap for improvement, or we cast Neuro (fairly slow recast, worst primary DD of casters that can DD) or ToM (fast but incredibly bad use of mana). Let's pretend you do damage via 50% DoT's and 50% DD's. If you have crit AA's for DD at 13% chance to crit your DPS increases by 6.5% on average, not 13% on average. A wizard casting only nukes with the same crit AA's (ie not maxed for them) would get an improvement of 13% on average.<br /><br />DPM point of view:<br />We either choose to cast a DoT with crap for improvement, or we cast Neuro (fairly slow recast, worst primary DD of casters that can DD) or ToM (fast but incredibly bad use of mana). Let's pretend that in a fight 50% of your mana goes towards DoT's and 50% towards DD's. If you have crit AA's for DD at 13% chance to crit your DPM increases by 6.5% on average, not 13% on average. A wizard casting only nukes with the same crit AA's (ie not maxed for them) would get an improvement of 13% DPM on average.<br /><br />Does this make sense? Our nukes will always be worse than a wizards (DPS and DPM) or mages (DPS and DPM) or enchanters (DPM) or shamans (DPM). Just give us the potential to improve ourselves as much as other damage classes.</span id="msg"></font></td>
